column1: Normal	Total cells from Patient 0092
column20: A	10X Genomics Chromium machine was used for single cell capture and cDNA was prepared using the Single Cell 3’ Protocol recommended by the manufacturer.
column21: The	10X Genomics Chromium machine partitions cells into Gel Bead-In-EMulsions (GEMs)
column22: where all generated cDNA share a common 10x Genomics barcode but uses a pool of about 750
column23: 000 barcodes to separately index each cell’s transcriptome. The R1 primers were added during the GEM incubation and the P5
column25: a sample index and R2 during library construction via end repair
column27: adaptor ligation and PCR. The final libraries contained the P5 and P7 primers used in Illumina bridge amplification. The sequencing was carried out on an Illumina NextSeq 500.
column29: Read	alignment and count summarization were performed using CellRanger v3.0.2 using the Illumina BCL files as input.
column31: Supplementary_files_format_and_content:	matrix.mtx files contain genewise read counts for all cells in the space-efficient matrix market format. The supplementary file features.tsv.gz contains the corresponding Ensembl IDs and gene symbols as tab-delimited text. The barcode.tsv files contain the 10X barcodes used to identify cells. Each matrix market file can be read into R
column33: using the read10X function of the edgeR software package.
column43: Walter	and Eliza Hall Institute of Medical Research

column21: The 10X Genomics Chromium machine partitions cells into Gel Bead-In-EMulsions (GEMs)
column22: where all generated cDNA share a common 10x Genomics barcode but uses a pool of about 750
column23: 000 barcodes to separately index each cell’s transcriptome. The R1 primers were added during the GEM incubation and the P5
column25: a sample index and R2 during library construction via end repair
column27: adaptor ligation and PCR. The final libraries contained the P5 and P7 primers used in Illumina bridge amplification. The sequencing was carried out on an Illumina NextSeq 500.
column29: Read alignment and count summarization were performed using CellRanger v3.0.2 using the Illumina BCL files as input.
column31: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: matrix.mtx files contain genewise read counts for all cells in the space-efficient matrix market format. The supplementary file features.tsv.gz contains the corresponding Ensembl IDs and gene symbols as tab-delimited text. The barcode.tsv files contain the 10X barcodes used to identify cells. Each matrix market file can be read into R
column33: using the read10X function of the edgeR software package.
column43: Walter and Eliza Hall Institute of Medical Research
